Phoenix police are investigating an Inquest case after skeletal remains were discovered in the bushes along the N2 freeway near the M25 interchange, recently. Communications officer at Phoenix SAPS Captain Louise Naidoo, said: “Members from Durban SAPS Search and Rescue along with Durban Metro Police Search And Rescue were called out to the N2 freeway near the M25 interchange where the skeletal remains of an unknown person was recovered from the bushes overlooking the freeway and handed over to members from Phoenix SAPS. An inquest has been opened.”